  "texts": [
    "We develop this argument from the literature on how researchers read and cite.",
    "When searching for papers to read carefully and potentially cite substantively, researchers focus primarily on quality, which they initially infer through status.",
    "As the status of a work grows with citations, it is more and more likely to attract such substantive attention.",
    "Teplitskiy et al.",
    "use surveys of authors to show that highly cited works attract disproportionally more substantive reading and citing and that the relationship between status and substantive attention is likely causal 9."
